$interpreted: Jahan: Old man Vincent, did you find our "services" satisfying? Just go ahead and admit that you're the mastermind behind the Regent's assassination.
Douglas: I-I won't... I swear on the Buck token of the Vincents. The Vincent family never had any intention to betray his Majesty Theodore...
Douglas: ...this is a false accusation!
Cecil: Out of my way! You filthy guards, how dare you stop me from visiting my father!
Jahan: Nailed the old one, now for the little brat.
Jahan: Looks like an opportunity to pay back Mister Cecil for what he did to me back at that party...
Cecil: You lowly dog! I warn you, let my father go right now!
Jahan: What are you gonna do about it?
Cecil: Father...forgive your son for being so worthless. Not only unable to free you from this wretched place...
Cecil: ...but humiliated by this lowly person!
Jahan: Young master of the Vincent family, I'm only...I am only doing this because of Sir Dylan's orders.
Cecil: Dylan Levon!? How dare he...
Jahan: I'm merely carrying out my superior's orders. In fact, I believe your father to be innocent.
Cecil: A-Are you serious?
Jahan: Don't you find it suspicious at all? The Vincent family's token of loyalty just so happens to be in Dylan's possession.
Jahan: And that just so happens to be the evidence against your father's alleged treason?
Cecil: You have a point, way too many coincidences...looks like I'll have to investigate some more...
Jahan: Go home and take a rest. I'll ask Sir Dylan to transfer your father to a better environment. We don't want him to get sick.
Jahan: Also, please don't mind that little conflict we had back there.
Cecil: Yes...I was indeed too impulsive. Jahan, thank you. I'm gonna look into this.
Jahan: Old man, have some water.
Douglas: ...Th-Thank you, Jahan...I...got you all wrong...
Jahan: No need to thank me. There was no misunderstanding.
Jahan: Now, now. Shall we announce that Sir Vincent committed suicide with poison in order to protect his reputation...
Jahan: ...or should we say he accidentally died under Sir Dylan's supervision?
